      About this item

      • EASY TO USE: No wiring, just plug in; Buckle design makes it easy to remove the remote switch from the plate; Also stick it to a wall with tape as a wall switch; Convenient for the elderly, pregnant women and disabled people
      • STRONG SIGNAL: Zoiinet remote switch controls your household appliances with one button, from anywhere in your home; The wireless range is up to 300 ft, which is enough to go through walls and windows; More convenient and efficient
      • DIY AS YOU WISH: Program and expand the wireless switch at will, enabling one switch to control multiple plugs at once or multiple switches to control one plug at once; Just one click to control all; Also work with Zoiinet's receiver and light socket
      • WIDE APPLICATION: Zoiinet 1500 W remote outlet can be used in a wide range of home appliances, including lights, electric ovens, fans, TV, humidifiers, heaters and more; It allows you to easily control appliances that are difficult to reach
      • CUSTOMER IS FIRST: UL, CE, FCC, RoHS, CQC, IP66, V0; Protect your family with multi-electrical safety; Remain off after a power outage; Battery in wireless switch lasts 10 years; Plug passed 400 K switching times tests; Free replacement if product defect

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5 out of 5 stars
      Handy Remote Control
      I have an overhead lamp that plugged into an outlet behind a couch, which makes it inaccessible to turn on/off. The Zoiinet remote control is just the right solution for that. It’s a good looking outlet adapter that comes with a remote control. The remote control work effortlessly and can be attached to a wall with the provided double side tapes. No Wi-Fi is needed. It’s very easy to install. Highly recommend.

      • Socks
        5.0 out of 5 stars Above average quality product!
        Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2025
        Style: 1 Switch 1 OutletVerified Purchase
        I needed 2 remotes set up in a manner that any of them would operate 2 different outlets at the same time. So, I got two sets of 1 remote and 1 outlet in each set. They re-programmed relatively easily to my specific needs, according to the included instruction leaflet.

        My setup: a long room with doors on either end, with an outlet by each door. Two lamps, each plugged in close to each door. I could re-program and add two remote switches, install them one by each door, to turn on and off both of the two lamps simultaneously.

        Pros:
        1. Aesthetics and ergonomics. Made w. attention to detail.
        2. Size and color make the remotes look like regular wall switches.
        3. Lithium battery CR2032 in remotes to last 5 to 10 years. Lithium batteries don't leak in my experience.
        4. Relatively easy programming and re-programming to suit multitude of setups and needs, with any number of outlets and switches.
        Cons:
        The only Con could be the price, higher than most other simple remote switches. But for the professional looks, the quality and versatility it's worth spending a little extra and enjoy it. So, the slightly higher price is not a Con. In this case you do get what you pay for, and it's worth it!
